  "prompt": "How do I avoid an awkward situation after a break up?",
  "response": "Here are some tips to avoid awkward situations after a breakup:\n\n1. Establish clear boundaries\n- Minimize contact\n- Avoid mutual social events if possible\n- Communicate respectfully but briefly\n\n2. Social media management\n- Consider unfollowing or muting them\n- Avoid posting passive-aggressive content\n- Resist the urge to stalk their profiles\n\n3. Mutual friends\n- Be mature and civil\n- Don't ask friends to take sides\n- Avoid discussing the breakup extensively\n\n4. Professional/academic settings\n- Maintain professionalism\n- Be polite but distant\n- Focus on your work/studies\n\n5. Emotional management\n- Process your feelings privately\n- Consider talking to a therapist or trusted friend\n- Avoid seeking revenge or creating drama\n\n6. Physical space\n- If you share living space, make exit plans\n- Return each other's belongings promptly\n- Minimize interactions during transition\n\n7. Self-care\n- Focus on personal growth\n- Engage in activities you enjoy\n- Spend time with supportive people\n\n8. Communication\n- If communication is necessary, keep it brief and neutral\n- Avoid emotional or accusatory language\n- Be direct and clear\n\nRemember, time and distance help heal and reduce awkwardness.",
